{"PageNumber":15,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":817,"Width":1089,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Software Quality Assurance vs Software Testing","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":27,"Y":63},"LeftTop":{"X":27,"Y":18},"RightBottom":{"X":791,"Y":63},"RightTop":{"X":791,"Y":18}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"title","Text":"##  Responsibility","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":94,"Y":248},"LeftTop":{"X":94,"Y":213},"RightBottom":{"X":284,"Y":248},"RightTop":{"X":284,"Y":213}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• Quality Assurance: QA is a responsibility shared by the entire development team, including project managers, developers, and testers. QA professionals provide guidance, establish processes, and monitor compliance with quality standards.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":119,"Y":426},"LeftTop":{"X":119,"Y":267},"RightBottom":{"X":1003,"Y":426},"RightTop":{"X":1003,"Y":267}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• Testing: Testing is primarily the responsibility of dedicated testers or testing teams. Their main role is to execute test cases, report defects, and ensure that the software meets the specified requirements.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":119,"Y":600},"LeftTop":{"X":119,"Y":442},"RightBottom":{"X":1003,"Y":600},"RightTop":{"X":1003,"Y":442}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"footer","Text":"14","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":1043,"Y":786},"LeftTop":{"X":1043,"Y":765},"RightBottom":{"X":1066,"Y":786},"RightTop":{"X":1066,"Y":765}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}